# EXAMPLE ONLY — this file is NOT loaded by Ansible (.example extension is ignored).
#
# Inventory SOPS is intentionally deferred (Pass 4 decision, 2026-06-24 — Option A).
# Rationale:
#   - The Flux deploy key is generated on the workstation (ssh-keygen, idempotent); putting it
#     here would turn a "regenerate, never stored" key into committed encrypted material.
#   - Inventory SOPS still requires a workstation age key to decrypt — it does not remove the
#     workstation dependency, only adds a plugin + inventory .sops.yaml on top.
#   - No per-host Ansible secret exists today that needs inventory encryption.
# Revisit this file ONLY when a real per-host Ansible secret (not a key or Kubernetes runtime
# secret) appears. Until then, the current-reality section below is the correct model.
#
# When you are ready to introduce encrypted inventory secrets:
#   1. Set a real age recipient in host/.sops.yaml (see that file).
#   2. Copy this file to secrets.sops.yml and fill in real values.
#   3. Encrypt it: SOPS_AGE_KEY_FILE=~/.homelab/local/atlas/flux/sops-age.key sops -e -i inventory/group_vars/homelab/secrets.sops.yml
#   4. Add community.sops to requirements.yml and enable the vars plugin in ansible.cfg:
#        vars_plugins_enabled = host_group_vars,community.sops.sops
#   5. Update any roles that should consume these vars instead of the current workstation-file lookup.
#
# Current reality (do NOT duplicate these until roles are rewired):
#   - flux_git_private_key      → generated on workstation by the flux role; NOT an inventory var yet.
#   - flux_sops_age_private_key → read from ~/.homelab/local/<host>/flux/sops-age.key by the flux role; NOT an inventory var yet.
#   - cloudflare_api_token      → encrypted Kubernetes manifest in homelab-cluster repo; decrypted in-cluster by Flux; NOT an inventory var.
#
# ---
# flux_git_private_key: |
#   -----BEGIN OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----
#   ...
#   -----END OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----
#
# flux_sops_age_private_key: |
#   AGE-SECRET-KEY-...
#
# cloudflare_api_token: "..."
